'''Importing Necessary libraries for model fitting'''

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
In [24]:
'''Defining the x,x1,x2 and y,y1,y2 variables'''

x=df.drop('diagnosis',axis=1)
y=df['diagnosis']
x1=df1.drop('diagnosis',axis=1)
y1=df1['diagnosis']
x2=df2.drop('diagnosis',axis=1)
y2=df2['diagnosis']
In [25]:
'''Splitting the dataframes into training and testing sets.'''

x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 0.3)
x1_train, x1_test, y1_train, y1_test = train_test_split(x1, y1, test_size = 0.3)
x2_train, x2_test, y2_train, y2_test = train_test_split(x2, y2, test_size = 0.3)
In [26]:
'''Importing the svm from sklearn'''

from sklearn.svm import SVC
In [27]:
'''Fitting the svm for df,df1,df2'''
